According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Flame Retardant Protective Clothing market was valued at USD 2.09 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 2.23 billion in 2025 to USD 3.17 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 6.3% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady growth due to increasingly stringent workplace safety regulations, including OSHA standards and NFPA guidelines, which mandate the use of flame-resistant personal protective equipment (PPE) in high-risk industries. Rising industrialization, particularly across the oil & gas, electrical utilities, manufacturing, and firefighting sectors, is further driving demand for advanced protective garments. Continuous innovations in lightweight, breathable, and moisture-wicking flame-resistant fabrics are also enhancing worker comfort without compromising safety.
